<h2> Math 235.4 : Introduction to Linear Algebra</h2>
<h3> Fall 2013 </h3>

This is the webpage for section 4 of Math 235. The course-wide webpage is <a href="http://www.math.umass.edu/~hacking/235F13common/">here</a>.
<br>
<br>

<b>Instructor</b>: Paul Hacking
<br>
<b>Email</b>: <a href="mailto:hacking@math.umass.edu">hacking@math.umass.edu</a>
<br>
<b>Office</b>: LGRT 1235H
<br>
<b>Office Hours</b>: Mondays 5:00PM--6:00PM and Tuesdays 4:00PM--5:00PM, in my office LGRT 1235H.
<br>
<b>Classes</b>: MWF 12:20PM--1:10PM in LGRT 171.
<br> 
<br>


<b>Textbook</b>
<p>
The course text is <i>Linear algebra with applications</i> by Otto Bretscher (4th or 5th ed.). <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=VAU8LgEACAAJ&dq=isbn:0321796942&hl=en&sa=X&ei=bngKUp_ICKrB4AOnjIDwCw&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA">googlebooks</a>.
</p>


<b>Syllabus</b>
<br>
<br>
(Numbers are sections from the textbook.)
<br>
<br>
Linear equations: 1.1 -- 1.3.
<br>
Linear transformations: 2.1 -- 2.4.
<br>
Subspaces of R<sup>n</sup> and their dimensions: 3.1 -- 3.4.
<br>
Linear spaces: 4.1 -- 4.3.
<br>
Determinants: 6.1 -- 6.3.
<br>
Eigenvalues and eigenvectors: 7.1 -- 7.5.
<br>
Orthogonality: 5.1, 5.2.
<br>
<br>
Detailed syllabus: <a href="235F13syllabus.pdf">pdf</a>.
<br>
<br>
Tentative schedule of classes <a href="schedule/index.html">here</a>.
